### 7. **Database Schema - reading_progress table** (`/c/Users/johnm/iskrib_v3/server/sql/stories.sql`, lines 78-87)

```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS reading_progress (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    user_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    story_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES stories(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    chapter_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES chapters(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    scroll_position REAL DEFAULT 0,              -- Percentage as 0-1 float
    last_read_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
    UNIQUE(user_id, story_id)                   -- One progress row per user per story
);

CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_reading_progress_user ON reading_progress(user_id);
```

**Key columns:**
- `scroll_position`: A float (0-1) representing scroll percentage, not absolute pixels
- `chapter_id`: The chapter the user was reading
- `last_read_at`: When they last read (updated on every progress save)
- Unique constraint on `(user_id, story_id)` ensures one progress row per user per story

